<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">October 1, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-october-1-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-243649 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/American_Cash-150x150.jpg" alt="money" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/books/a62394281/who-pays-for-the-arts/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Kate Dwyer looks into the crisis of arts funding in the U.S.</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://thebaffler.com/latest/beyond-baby-blues-mcallen?utm_source%3Drss-feed%26utm_medium%3Drss%26utm_campaign%3Dfeed" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">An American history of postpartum depression</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.atlasobscura.com/articles/who-is-baba-yaga" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">A brief history of Baba Yaga</span></a></li>
</ul>
